clinicalSynopsis.miscellaneous:
Onset in infancy or early childhood {UMLS:C1837138};
Episodes occur 30 minutes to 3 hours after exposure to cold {UMLS:C2675796};
Episodes usually last 1 to 2 days {UMLS:C2675797};
See also Muckle-Wells syndrome ({191900}), an allelic disorder with overlapping features
